   "source": [
    "# Session 5 further work"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# We always start with appropriate imports; note the use of the IPython magic\n",
    "# command to set up Matplotlib within the notebook\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Matrix approach to boundary-value problems\n",
    "\n",
    "### Question 1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def cross_sec_area(x):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Return cross-sectional area of bar pi*(2-x)**2/10000\"\"\"\n",
    "    return np.pi*(2-x)*(2-x)/10000.0"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[[-0.00236  0.0011   0.       0.       0.       0.       0.     ]\n",
      " [ 0.0011  -0.00207  0.00096  0.       0.       0.       0.     ]\n",
      " [ 0.       0.00096 -0.00179  0.00083  0.       0.       0.     ]\n",
      " [ 0.       0.       0.00083 -0.00154  0.00071  0.       0.     ]\n",
      " [ 0.       0.       0.       0.00071 -0.0013   0.00059  0.     ]\n",
      " [ 0.       0.       0.       0.       0.00059 -0.00108  0.00049]\n",
      " [ 0.       0.       0.       0.       0.       0.00049 -0.00089]]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "N = 7\n",
    "delta_x = 1.0/(N+1)\n",
    "M = np.zeros((N,N))\n",
    "stencil = np.array([1.,-2.,1.])\n",
    "for i in range(1,N-1):\n",
    "    x = delta_x*i\n",
    "    Ax = cross_sec_area(x)\n",
    "    Axp = cross_sec_area(x+delta_x)\n",
    "    stencil = np.array([Ax,-Ax-Axp,Axp])\n",
    "    M[i,i-1:i+2] = stencil\n",
    "x = 0.0\n",
    "Ax = cross_sec_area(x)\n",
    "Axp = cross_sec_area(x+delta_x)\n",
    "stencil = np.array([Ax,-Ax-Axp,Axp])\n",
    "M[0,0:2] = stencil[1:3]\n",
    "x = (N-1)*delta_x\n",
    "Ax = cross_sec_area(x)\n",
    "Axp = cross_sec_area(x+delta_x)\n",
    "stencil = np.array([Ax,-Ax-Axp,Axp])\n",
    "M[N-1,N-2:N] = stencil[0:2]\n",
    "np.set_printoptions(precision=5)\n",
    "print(M)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0.5,1,'Temperature in varying bar')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "b = np.zeros(N)\n",
    "b[0] = -500*cross_sec_area(0.0)\n",
    "b[N-1] = -300*cross_sec_area(1.0-delta_x) # This needs to be x+delta_x for x=delta_x*(N-1)\n",
    "theta = np.dot(np.linalg.inv(M),b)\n",
    "theta_full = np.zeros(N+2)\n",
    "theta_full[0] = 500\n",
    "theta_full[1:N+1] = theta\n",
    "theta_full[N+1] = 300\n",
    "x = np.linspace(0,1,N+2)\n",
    "plt.plot(x,theta_full)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Distance in m')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Temperature in K')\n",
    "plt.title('Temperature in varying bar')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Parabolic equations\n",
    "\n",
    "### Question 1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def calc_M(N,zeta):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calculate matrix M for Crank-Nicolson solution of heat equation\n",
    "    Inputs: \n",
    "    N    size of matrix\n",
    "    zeta parameter\n",
    "    Outputs:\n",
    "    (NxN) matrix\"\"\"\n",
    "    output = np.zeros((N,N))\n",
    "    stencil = np.array([-zeta, 2*(1.0+zeta),-zeta])\n",
    "    for i in range(1,N-1):\n",
    "        output[i,i-1:i+2] = stencil\n",
    "    output[0,0:2] = stencil[1:3]\n",
    "    output[N-1,N-2:N] = stencil[0:2]\n",
    "    return output"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def calc_N(N,zeta):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calculate matrix M for Crank-Nicolson solution of heat equation\n",
    "    Inputs: \n",
    "    N    size of matrix\n",
    "    zeta parameter\n",
    "    Outputs:\n",
    "    (NxN) matrix\"\"\"\n",
    "    output = np.zeros((N,N))\n",
    "    stencil = np.array([zeta, 2*(1.0-zeta),zeta])\n",
    "    for i in range(1,N-1):\n",
    "        output[i,i-1:i+2] = stencil\n",
    "    output[0,0:2] = stencil[1:3]\n",
    "    output[N-1,N-2:N] = stencil[0:2]\n",
    "    return output"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[[ 3.  -0.5  0.   0.   0. ]\n",
      " [-0.5  3.  -0.5  0.   0. ]\n",
      " [ 0.  -0.5  3.  -0.5  0. ]\n",
      " [ 0.   0.  -0.5  3.  -0.5]\n",
      " [ 0.   0.   0.  -0.5  3. ]]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "matM = calc_M(5,0.5)\n",
    "print(matM)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[[1.  0.5 0.  0.  0. ]\n",
      " [0.5 1.  0.5 0.  0. ]\n",
      " [0.  0.5 1.  0.5 0. ]\n",
      " [0.  0.  0.5 1.  0.5]\n",
      " [0.  0.  0.  0.5 1. ]]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "matN = calc_N(5,0.5)\n",
    "print(matN)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Question 2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "N = 7\n",
    "zeta = 0.5\n",
    "matM = calc_M(N-2,zeta)\n",
    "matN = calc_N(N-2,zeta)\n",
    "matMinv = np.linalg.inv(matM)\n",
    "b = np.zeros(N-2)\n",
    "b[0] = 2*zeta*500\n",
    "b[-1] = 2*zeta*300\n",
    "matMinvN = np.dot(matMinv,matN)\n",
    "matMinvb = np.dot(matMinv,b)\n",
    "Nt = 40\n",
    "temperature = np.zeros((Nt,N-2))\n",
    "temperature[0] = 300\n",
    "for n in range(1,Nt):\n",
    "    temperature[n] = matMinvb + np.dot(matMinvN,temperature[n-1])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0.5,1,'Crank-Nicolson solutions for bar (zeta=0.5)')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 10,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {

     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"

   ],
   "source": [
    "x = np.linspace(1/6,5/6,5)\n",

    "plt.xlabel('x in m')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Temperature in K')\n",
    "plt.title('Crank-Nicolson solutions for bar (zeta=0.5)')"
   ]

    "zeta = 2.0\n",

    "Nt = 10\n",
    "temperature = np.zeros((Nt,N-2))\n",
    "temperature[0] = 300\n",
    "for n in range(1,Nt):\n",
    "    temperature[n] = matMinvb + np.dot(matMinvN,temperature[n-1])"
